"6:101:18" : {s: 6, a: 101, w: 18, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمٌۭ", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīmun", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী",e: "All-Knower", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", i: "Maha Mengetahui", f: 100, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
